parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front seat belt retractor can lead to a loss of seat belt functionality, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front seat belt retractor fails to retract
the seat belt remains fully extended
the seat belt retracts slowly
the seat belt requires manual assistance to retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes grab or lock up intermittently
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle slides or fails to stop when the brakes are applied
the brake fluid leaks onto the wheels
and the brake lines/hoses are damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear wheel cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of stopping power and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
and brake fluid leaks onto the wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent windshield wiper operation can reduce visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers work intermittently
wipers stop working and then start again after a few hours
wiper system appears "frozen".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Windshield delamination can cause reduced visibility, increased risk of injury from shattered glass, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Windshield is delaminating
cracks or bubbles appear on the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Vehicle Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause vehicle fires, which can result in serious injury or death, as well as significant property damage.
symptoms: Engine compartment fire
interior fire
shorted battery cables
electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rupture of the transmission cooler line can cause transmission failure, leading to a loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: Transmission failure
transmission slipping
transmission overheating
smoke or fire coming from the engine compartment
transmission fluid leaking onto the exhaust manifold.
